    <h1 class="about-header2">A little bit more about me</h1>
    <p class="about-body">
      If you haven't yet figured out from the photos, my other passion is avaiation. I still have the image in my mind of the first time I saw an aeroplane, at the airport, aged five,
      whilst holding my mothers hand. After leaving my job, I took some time out to finish my private pilots training and get my license.
      The photo above left, was taken on the day I first solo'ed, having only one and a half weeks training. It's one of the greatest days of my life.</p>
    <p class="about-body">
      Another passion of mine is travelling. After uni, I spent one year backpacking across twenty-one countries, spanning three continents. During my travels
      I climbed an active volcano in Chile, scuba dived on the Great Barrier Reef, swam with dolphins in New Zealand, travelled to Ushuaia in Argentina,
      the southernmost city in the world, visited Machu Picchu, climbed the Great Wall of China, visited The Forbidden City in Beijing,
      was dazzled at the beauty of the The Taj Mahal, drank tea in Darjeeling, trekked in the Himalayas, took a cooking class Chang Mai, was touched by the kindness of the Vietnamese,
      humbled at Angkor Wat and saddened visiting the 'killing fields' in Phnom Phen.
      </p>
